text: Captain Donald Edward "Don" Williams (February 13, 1942 â€“ February 23, 2016) was an American naval officer and aviator, test pilot, mechanical engineer and NASA astronaut. He has a recorded total of 287 hours and 35 minutes in space. He was born in Lafayette, Indiana. Williams died on February 23, 2016 in Fort Lauderdale, Florida from complications of a stroke.
